==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: optical activity
<hw>optical activity</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>the
ability of a chemical compound to rotate the plane of plane-polarized
light. This is found only in chemicals whose molecular structure does
not have a plane of symmetry, and is common in biochemical
compounds.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>optically active</wf>
<pos>adj.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>optical cable</ent>⟦br⟧
